# PWA & Capacitor Android

## PWA (`vite.config.ts`)

- `vite-plugin-pwa` : `registerType: 'autoUpdate'`, `devOptions.enabled: false`
- Manifest : `start_url: '/app'`, `theme_color: '#D4789A'`
- Workbox : `navigateFallback: '/index.html'`, cache GraphQL en **NetworkFirst**

## Capacitor 8

- `androidScheme: 'https'` → origine app `https://localhost`
- Build : `npm run build:android` (= vite build + cap sync + patch AGP 8.2.2)

## Guards plateforme

```ts
import { Capacitor } from '@capacitor/core'

if (Capacitor.isNativePlatform() && Capacitor.getPlatform() === 'android') {
  // Health Connect, Wear, ML Kit barcode…
}
```

- Bridges : import dynamique du plugin (`health-connect-bridge.ts`, `wear-bridge.ts`)
- Web : no-op ou overlay PWA (ex. `PwaBarcodeScannerOverlay` vs `NativeBarcodeScannerOverlay`)
- **Pas de support iOS** sauf demande explicite

## APIs externes

- Open Food Facts : proxy Vite en web ; fonction Nhost en natif (`open-food-facts.ts`)

## Anti-patterns

- Import top-level d'un plugin Capacitor sans guard (casse le bundle web)
- OAuth Google dans la WebView principale
- PWA dev activée (reste `false`)
